                            <comment id="226313" author="adilger" created="Thu, 19 Apr 2018 03:46:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This appears to be true for any composite layout (i.e. using &lt;tt&gt;-E&lt;/tt&gt;), regardless of whether DoM is used or not.  Using &lt;tt&gt;lfs setstripe&lt;/tt&gt; with a plain layout (e.g. only &lt;tt&gt;-c2&lt;/tt&gt;) prints an error &quot;stripe already set&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
